<h2>decktech.net</h2><b>location of article:</b> <hr>Qualifying for SW:CCG Worlds 2002 posted by DeckTech on Mon Feb 18 2002 <br><img src="/groups/global/images/sw.gif" align=left>The players committee has decided against State Championship qualifications instead they opted for the old Regional Qualification system. I know what you&#8217;re thinking, &#8220;Ughh, I have to drive an extra 600 miles to even play?&#8221; But remember, we are talking about a chance at winning $5,000!<br>
<br>
From April to July, Regional Championships will be held with both finalists getting byes into Day Two of the SWCCG World Championships.  These regions will also be used for qualification for Young Jedi and Jedi Knights World Championship as well. <br>
<br>
In addition the five major summer conventions (Origins, GenCon, DragonCon, SanDeigo ComicCon, and Essen) will play host to five Open Championships where the top two competitors will also get byes into Day Two of the SWCCG World Championships.<br>
<br>
Both Bastian Winkelhaus and Matt Sokol will be awarded Day Two byes.  Matt won the SWCCG World Championships at DecipherCon 2000.  Bastian won the SWCCG World Championship last year at FreedomCon.  Both players reign, as champions, will be honored.<br>
<br>
If you want to volunteer or sponsor an event, please be sure to contact John Arendt (littlejohn@idcomm.com)he will assist you with what you need. <br>
<br>
We have had numerous requests to post regional information on DeckTech. In order to consolidate all of this information we are going to post the information for all regionals at once. <br>
<br>
If you want your regional to be listed on the DeckTech Website send your information to littlejohn@idcomm.com. Some things to include are: Date, location, time, contact info, and link to your DeckTech Group about that regional or other website.<br>
<br>
Stay tuned here for more information about SW:CCG 2002 and the new printable cards that the players committee is extensively play testing/producing right now. <br>
<br>
Soon you will be able to print out new game text for your favorite characters and slip it over your old cards! These cards will be tournament legal so keep your eyes open!<br>
<br>
