<hr>Sean Smallman said on Thu Feb 28 2002 <br>Steve,<br>
<br>
The $10,000 for the SW World Championships this fall is not a sales incentive.  Since we have pretty much sold all of our remaining inventory already, there is nothing to be gained by putting up this money, other than the good will of you players.  We want to show that we stand with you guys.  And, while it is true and has been admitted that we knew there was a chance we would lose the license a long time ago, that was not fact yet and we were unwilling to roll over for Hasbro.  Everybody heard the rumors, but until late 2001 they were only rumors.  We believed that Lucas could be persuaded to keep us on and fought to keep the game going under Decipher even up to the end of last year.  While the hope was getting smaller, we were not allowed to discuss it by contract with Lucas, so don't think that we were trying to deceive anybody.  I know you think of Decipher as a greedy corporation based on your comments, but if you really knew us you would think otherwise.  We are a business, but one that is very concientous of the playing community.  I wouldn't work for Decipher if that were not true.  I would not have left teaching middle school for over 8 years to work for a company that just wanted to take money from kids.  Its easy to blame a faceless corporation, but we are gamers and nice people.  The kind that still show up for tournaments just to play.<hr>Mitch Velasco said on Thu Feb 28 2002 <br>Sorry for the clarification.  Only the WINNER of Florida Conquest Open gets a seat at Worlds.<br>
